cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.HC 

This paper discusses the negative consequences of overemphasizing metrics in AI development, which is a central aspect of most current AI approaches. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI. The paper also discusses how our online environment and current business practices exacerbate these failures, which could fall under cs.CY (computers and society) and cs.SI (social and information networks). The paper also looks at real-world case studies, which could fall under cs.CR (cryptography and security) and cs.HC (human-computer interaction).
